  "prompt": "Where is the cheapest place to buy vitamin B-12 near or on University of Washington campus?",
  "response": "When looking for the cheapest place to buy vitamin B-12 near the University of Washington campus, consider checking out the following options:\n\n1. **University District Farmers Market**: This market is held on Saturdays and may have a vendor selling health supplements, though prices and availability can vary.\n\n2. **Grocery Stores**:\n   - **Safeway**: Located at 3020 Northeast 45th Street, this store often has sales and a rewards program that can help reduce the price of vitamins.\n   - **QFC (Quality Food Centers)**: There are multiple locations near the campus, such as the one at 4500 40th Ave NE. They typically offer a range of vitamins and have discounts and rewards for members.\n\n3. **Retail Pharmacies**:\n   - **Rite Aid**: Located at 10002 14th Ave NW, Rite Aid often has vitamins on sale and carries store-brand options which can be cheaper.\n   - **Walgreens**: With multiple locations around the university area, Walgreens frequently offers discounts and deals on vitamins through their app and loyalty program.\n\n4. **Online Retailers**: Consider checking Amazon or Walmart online for potentially lower prices, and you can have them delivered, sometimes with same-day or next-day shipping.\n\n5. **Local Co-ops** and **Health Stores**: \n   - **PCC Community Markets**: Located at 4500 NE 40th Street, PCC has a selection of vitamins and often supports local health products.\n   - **Whole Foods Market**: At 1026 NE 64th Street, Whole Foods offers a variety of supplements, though they may be pricier.\n\nComparing prices between these locations, looking for sales or specials, and considering generic or store-brand options can help you find the cheapest vitamin B-12. Additionally, joining loyalty or rewards programs can potentially offer further savings.",
